    <h4 style="text-align: center">Informed Consent</h4>
    Confidentiality.
    <p>When engaging with a 4NTENT Health Mentor or service through 4NTENT’s platforms all discussions that occur within sessions are kept in confidence. Any information, names, relationships, or concerns you share remain confident. Due to the nature of your wellness profile, the health mentors you choose will be in collaboration with one another. You can amend these health mentors at any time or revoke their ability to collaborate. If your safety or someone else’s safety is in question we has health mentors are mandated reporters and we may reach out to your family/friends in emergencies or call 911 if necessary. If you’d like further information shared, please review this process with your health mentor or use the invite a friend feature to connect through out platform. You may designate who you would like information shared with and you may invite whoever you like into your wellness profile.You are responsible for reading and agreeing to 4NTENT’s privacy agreement. Please be aware that if we communicate via email, text, or online, your information may not be protected and you will be running the risk of exposure. There are technological risks that may occur during sessions such as session ending due to poor connection, delay in video/sound, to name a few. You agree to these potential risks and to provide feedback regarding your experience so that 4NTENT can improve the technology used. Hypothetically the system administrator would have access to these past logs or conversations and sites can be hacked.</p>
    <p>If you engage in a family program with 4NTENT health mentors but decide to take advantage of a few individual sessions please know that what you bring up in your individual session will also be included in the families programming. Please do not disclose anything to our health mentors that you would not also want to share with your family. This is 4NTENT’s “no secret” policy. If you engage in teen programs please keep in mind that what a teen shares will not always be shared with parents to build confidence, rapport, and trust with 4NTENT’s team. Required Reporting and ensuring your Safety: All 4NTENT’s health mentors serve as mandated reporters. If we have any reason to believe that you or someone you know may be in danger, in a crisis, or your safety is at risk we have the right to seek out information from your family and friends to ensure your safety. If we feel you are a danger to yourself or someone else we will be contacting your friends, family and the police to ensure safety for all parties involved.</p>
    <p>If there is any reason to believe that abuse or neglect of a child or minor is occurring, most of our health mentors are mandated reporters and are required to report to the child protective services or to local law enforcement (police or sheriff’s department) immediately by phone. A written report must then be sent within 36 hours by fax, or it may be sent by electronic submission, if a secure system has been made available for that purpose. Written reports must be submitted on the California Suspected Child Abuse Report Form 8572. If a minor reports having non-consensual sexual contact our health mentors will review what is legal and appropriate and will take action of reporting to authorities in compliance with California state laws. If you report any form of abuse or inappropriate conduct from another named health care provider or counselor we are required to report this to the provider’s existing board and the California Department of Health.</p>
    <br>
    Your Wellness Profile.
    <p>All of your records within the wellness profile are password protected and set up by you at the beginning of your engagement with 4NTENT. You may always change your password, delete your account, and or ask for support to locate past data. Our account administrator has access to information that is stored so please only share information you are comfortable with in your profile section. We advise our health mentors to only take minimal notes during sessions which disclose the main topics of education who attended, and the plan for following sessions. If you wish to have the health mentor refrain from taking notes please inform us of this request in writing and we will keep this in your record. 4NTENT does not get involved with court related proceedings due to divorce or custody disputes.</p>
    <p>Information contained in your wellness profile is confidential and protected to the best of our ability. Information you enter into your wellness profile is the only information that your chosen health mentors will see in addition to your comments during 1:1 programs or group programs. If you’d like further insights to be shared with an outside medical provider we would ask that a release of information is signed. 4NTENT does not interact or accept insurance so information is not disclosed for payment to 3rd parties. 4NTENT does utilize PayPal as a payment interface so your information may be at risk if PayPal experiences a breech of data.</p>
    <p>Complaints or Lawsuits: if you file a complaint or lawsuit against us, we must provide any requested information or any information relating to the health mentor’s defense of him/herself.</p>
